{"lemma":"فِطْرَةُ","slug":"فِطْرَةُ","root":"ف.ط.ر","root_slug":"ف-ط-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ط-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adv","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n34127","n34128","n34135"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%90%D8%B7%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"creation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"nature, disposition, constitution, temperament, instinct"},{"pos":"adv","gloss":"by nature"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fungus, mushroom","tags":["singulative"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Ge'ez ፍጥረት (fəṭrät, “creation; nature, disposition”) together with فَطَرَ (faṭara, “to create”) from ፈጠረ (fäṭärä, “to create; to inscribe, to carve”), unless – which cannot be excluded –, independently shaped from the borrowed verb, which is however unlikely considering the semantic and morphic parallelism.\n\nAdverbial accusative of فِطْرَة (fiṭra).\n\nSingulative noun of فُطْر (fuṭr, “fungus, mushroom”). Compare Hebrew פִּטְרִיָּה (pitriyá)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34127","headword_ar":"فَطَرَهُ","root":"fTr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K, TA,) and, accord. to the K,"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, but this latter form requires consideration, for it is related by Sgh, from Fr, in another sense, that of milking a camel, and not unrestrictedly, (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faTorN","text_ar":"فَطْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fT~rhu","text_ar":"فطّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tafoTiyrN","text_ar":"تَفْطِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) [but the latter is with teshdeed to denote muchness, or frequency, or repetition, of the action, or its application to many objects;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He clave, split, slit, rent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cracked, it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K.) ―         -b2-  Hence, (S,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faTara","text_ar":"فَطَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faTorN","text_ar":"فَطْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuTuwrN","text_ar":"فُطُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the tooth called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nAb","text_ar":"ناب"},{"kind":"text","text":", of a camel,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came forth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it clave the flesh and came forth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  See also 7.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faTarahu","text_ar":"فَطَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faTorN","text_ar":"فَطْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(God, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"created it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,) namely, the creation: (Msb, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he caused it to exist, produced it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brought it into existence, newly, for the first time, it not having existed before; originated it; commenced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"began it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, Mgh, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AftTrhu","text_ar":"افتطرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", relating to an affair. (TA.) I'Ab says, I did not know what is [the meaning of]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~am`waAti","text_ar":"السَّمٰوَاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faATiru","text_ar":"فَاطِرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Originater,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Creator, of the heavens"},{"kind":"text","text":"] until two Arabs of the desert came to me, disputing together respecting a well, and one of them said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA faTarotuhaA","text_ar":"اَنَا فَطَرْتُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I originated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"began, it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuTira","text_ar":"فُطِرَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"عَلَى الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TubiEa","text_ar":"طُبِعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". [The explanation there given is confirmed by explanations of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiTorapN","text_ar":"فِطْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faTara AlEajiyna","text_ar":"فَطَرَ العَجِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faTorN","text_ar":"فَطْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fTr~hu","text_ar":"فطرّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Ks, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made the dough into bread,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"baked it, without leavening it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leaving it until it should become good"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mature"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he kneaded the dough and made it into bread,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"baked it, immediately;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he hurried the dough,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prepared it hastily, so as to prevent its becoming mature."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faTarat A@lomaroA^apu","text_ar":"فَطَرَت ا@لْمَرْاَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEajiyna Hat~aY A@sotabaAna fiyhi AlfaToru","text_ar":"العَجِينَ حَتَّى ا@سْتَبَانَ فِيهِ الفَطْرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The woman hurried the dough,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prepared it hastily, so that immaturity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"want of leaven, was manifest in it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b2-  And in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faTara AlT~iyna","text_ar":"فَطَرَ الطِّينَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He prepared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kneaded, the clay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mud,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without leaving it until it should become mature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and plastered with it immediately."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faTara Aljiloda","text_ar":"فَطَرَ الجِلْدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faTorN","text_ar":"فَطْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfTrhu","text_ar":"افطرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He did not saturate the skin with the tanning liquid:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he did not put it therein."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.)       -A4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faTara","text_ar":"فَطَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, O, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, O, K, * TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faTorN","text_ar":"فَطْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He milked"},{"kind":"text","text":"a she-camel, (Fr, S, O, K,) and a ewe or goat, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the fore finger and the thumb:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S, O, K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the ends of the fingers:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or, as one does in indicating the number thirty, i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the two thumbs and the two fore fingers:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[but this is app. a mistake for what next follows:] (L, TA:) or, accord. to IAth,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with two fingers"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the end of the thumb."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dab~a Aln~aAqapa","text_ar":"ضَبَّ النَّاقَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2416},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b2-  And [hence, app.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faTara A^aSaAbiEahu","text_ar":"فَطَرَ اَصَابِعَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pressed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"squeezed, his fingers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He struck his"},{"kind":"text","text":"(another's)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fingers so that they burst forth with blood"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AinofaTarato damFA","text_ar":"اِنْفَطَرَتْ دَمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (TA.)       -A5-  See also 2: ―         -b2-  and 4, first sentence."}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","TA","Msb","Mgh","God","Lth","IAar","Fr","O","L"]},{"entry_id":"n34128","headword_ar":"فطّرهُ","root":"fTr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, first sentence.       -A2-  Also, (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tafoTiyrN","text_ar":"تَفْطِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him to break his fast;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to eat and drink;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Mgh, * K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfTrhu","text_ar":"افطرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faTarahu","text_ar":"فَطَرَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he gave him breakfast: he,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(namely, the action termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isotimonaA='N","text_ar":"اـِسْتِمْنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and a clyster, [&c.,] Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broke,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vitiated, his fast."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And you say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA kalaAmN yufoTiru AlS~awoma","text_ar":"هٰذَا كَلَامٌ يُفْطِرُ الصَّوْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [and, more commonly,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yufaT~iruhu","text_ar":"يُفَطِّرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is speech which breaks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vitiates, the fast."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fT~r","text_ar":"فطّر"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEajiyna","text_ar":"العَجِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1."}],"source_refs":["K"]},{"entry_id":"n34135","headword_ar":"فِطْرَةٌ","root":"fTr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Creation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"causing"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to exist, producing"},{"kind":"text","text":"it, or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bringing"},{"kind":"text","text":"it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into existence, newly, for the first time; originating"},{"kind":"text","text":"it. (TA.) ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"natural constitution with which a child is created in his mother's womb;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiloqapN","text_ar":"خِلْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Mgh.) It is said to have this signification in the Kur xxx. 29. (TA.) And so in the saying of Mohammad,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~u mawoluwdK yuwladu EalaY","text_ar":"كُلُّ مَوْلُودٍ يُولَدُ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfiTorapi","text_ar":"الفِطْرَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Every infant is born in a state of conformity to the natural constitution with which he is created in his mother's womb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prosperous"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unprosperous"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in relation to the soul"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and if his parents are Jews, they make him a Jew, with respect to his worldly predicament; [i. e., with respect to inheritances &c.;] and if Christians, they make him a Christian, with respect to that predicament; and if Magians, they make him a Magian, with respect to that predicament; his predicament is the same as that of his parents until his tongue speaks for him: but if he die before his attaining to the age when virility begins to show itself, he dies in a state of conformity to his preceding natural constitution, with which he was created in his mother's womb. (AHeyth, TA.) [See another explanation of the word, as occurring in this trad., below.] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nature; constitution;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"natural, native, innate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"original, disposition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"temper"},{"kind":"text","text":"or other"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"property; idiosyncrasy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, TA.) ―         -b4-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faculty of knowing God, with which He has created mankind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"natural constitution with which a child is created in his mother's womb, whereby he is capable of accepting the religion of truth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"this is a secondary application: and this is [said to be] the signification meant in the trad. mentioned above. (Mgh.) ―         -b5-  Hence, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"religion of el-Islám:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"profession whereby a man becomes a Muslim, which is the declaration that there is no deity but God, and that Mohammad is his servant and his apostle, who brought the truth from Him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and this is (AHeyth, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"religion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, K, TA.) This is shown by a trad., in which it is related that Mohammad taught a man to repeat certain words when lying down to sleep, and said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA_in~aka A_ino mut~a mino layolatika","text_ar":"فَاـِنَّكَ اـِنْ مُتَّ مِنْ لَيْلَتِكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mut~a EalaY AlfiTorapi","text_ar":"مُتَّ عَلَى الفِطْرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And then, if thou die that same night, thou diest in the profession of the true religion"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (AHeyth, TA.) Also by the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaS~u","text_ar":"قَصُّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aZofaAri mina AlfiTorapi","text_ar":"الاَظْفَارِ مِنَ الفِطْرَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The paring of the nails is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a point"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the religion of el-Islám."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) ―         -b6-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sun~apN","text_ar":"سُنَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way, course, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of acting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, pursued, and prescribed to be followed, by Mohammad"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b7-  In the Kur xxx. 29, accord. to some, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covenant received,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accepted, from Adam and his posterity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd.) ―         -b8-  The pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiTaraAtN","text_ar":"فِطَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiToraAtN","text_ar":"فِطْرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiTiraAtN","text_ar":"فِطِرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiTorN","text_ar":"فِطْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Msb","TA","Mgh","AHeyth"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}